sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Teamshares files draft S-4 for merger with Live Oak Acquisition Corp V
feed.summary: Teamshares Inc., a technology-enabled acquirer of small businesses, has confidentially submitted a draft registration statement on Form S-4 for its proposed business combination with Live Oak Acquisition Corp. V (NASDAQ:LOKV). The combined entity will operate as Teamshares and list on Nasdaq under tickers "TMS" and "TMSW" upon completion of the transaction, which was initially announced on November 14, 2025. Teamshares, founded in 2019, acquires businesses with $0.5 to $5 million in EBITDA from retiring owners and implements employee stock ownership programs.

feed.title: Live Oak V Submits Confidential S-4 for Anticipated Teamshares Nasdaq Listing
feed.summary: Teamshares and Live Oak Acquisition Corp. V have confidentially submitted a draft Form S-4 registration statement to the SEC for a proposed business combination. The combined entity will operate as "Teamshares Inc." and intends to list its securities on Nasdaq under the tickers "TMS" and "TMSW." This transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, follows an agreement announced on November 14, 2025, for Teamshares to acquire Live Oak V.

feed.title: Teamshares Inc. agreed to acquire Live Oak Acquisition Corp. V in a reverse merger transaction.
feed.summary: Teamshares Inc. has agreed to acquire Live Oak Acquisition Corp. V (NasdaqGM:LOKV) in a reverse merger transaction, which includes $126 million in committed common equity PIPE financing. The deal, unanimously approved by both boards, is expected to close in the second quarter of 2026. This transaction will result in Teamshares Inc. becoming a Nasdaq-listed company.

feed.title: Teamshares To Go Public Via SPAC Merger Deal With Live Oak
feed.summary: Teamshares Inc. will merge with SPAC Live Oak Acquisition Corp. V, valuing the combined company at $746 million. The deal includes $126 million in PIPE funding and intends to list the combined entity, "Teamshares Inc.," on Nasdaq under the ticker "TMS" in Q2 2026. This merger allows Teamshares to continue acquiring small businesses and offers employees stock ownership, providing an exit strategy for retiring owners.
